{"_id":"b3139a90-207d-11ec-b3a5-91af1836e3f1","postId":"2013_01_async-oop-3-properties-a63cc351-e3f4-3a7c-be7a-928114355720","postUri":"https://blog.stephencleary.com/2013/01/async-oop-3-properties.html","replyTo":"","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"4ead14f3d279144d5ad5946d2e0b4b2f","authorName":"SG","authorUri":"","message":"What I dislike about these approaches is it defeats my primary purpose of using properties w/ getters - encapsulation and organization. I don't want all of my properties implemented in a giant thousand-line constructor. I want their definitions, which are interdependent in many cases, to be well-separated. So if I want to see the implementation of a field, I know exactly where to look.","date":"2021-09-28T17:01:19.110Z"}